Perl 5.10.0:

# On 10/27/2008, I tried to download ActivePerl for Linux, but there was an
# http error (bad URL, I guess).

cd ~/tmp
wget http://www.cpan.org/src/perl-5.10.0.tar.gz
tar zxf perl-5.10.0.tar.gz
cd perl-5.10.0
# To run interactively, omit "-de"
sh Configure -de
make
make test
sudo make install


===========================================================================

Perl 5.8.0 on Red Hat Linux:

Run all of this on geyer; it didn't work to do the build on a client and
the install on geyer, because of different /usr/include/bits/ files.

# This might not work sometimes because of "redirection to itself".
# Or run it on a machine besides geyer.
(cd ~/tmp; wget http://perl.com/CPAN/src/stable.tar.gz)
cd ~/tmp
mv stable.tar.gz perl-5.8.0.tar.gz
tar zxf perl-5.8.0.tar.gz
cd perl-5.8.0
rm -f config.sh Policy.sh
sh Configure -de
make
make test
sudo make install
(cd /usr/include && sudo h2ph *.h sys/*.h)
sudo installhtml --help
# (cd pod && make tex  && <process the latex files>)

# Install info pages.
# As of 7/2004, Perl 5.6.1 versions (made 3/2001) are the most recent.
cd ~/tmp
wget ftp://ftp.cpan.org/pub/CPAN/doc/manual/texinfo/perl5/perl-5.6-info.tar.gz
tar zxvf perl-5.6-info.tar.gz
cd perl-5.6-info/info
rm *unsplit*
# On pag, these "/usr/local" are "/usr/local/share" instead.
sudo cp -pf * /usr/local/info
sudo emacs /usr/local/info/dir
# Add the following 3 lines to the dir file:
Perl
* Perl: (perl).         Practical Extraction and Reporting Language.
* Perl moduldes: (pm).  Perl modules.




## Now rebuild/reinstall perl modules that need to be.  In particular,
## I must reinstall spamassassin immediately if I'm upgrading to a version
## of Perl that is not binary-compatible, because spamassasin hard-codes
## the Perl libraries.


While building on geyer, I got two test failures in "make test".
I ignored them.  (There were no errors when I built on the client machines,
but then I couldn't install on geyer.)

op/groups..............................FAILED test 1                         
        Failed 1/2 tests, 50.00% okay
op/lfs.................................FAILED tests 6, 8, 10, 12             
        Failed 4/17 tests, 76.47% okay

