Configure -d
  Actually, I did Configure and gave the default answer everywhere, except
  that I added -DDEBUGGING.  But that has to do with debugging Perl, not
  debugging Perl scripts, so I really didn't need to.
make depend
   Hints say:
    MIPS machines may need to undef d_volatile.
    MIPS machines may need to turn off -O on some files.
    Some MIPS machines may need to undefine CASTNEGFLOAT.
make
   I got some cfe warnings
make test
doit make install

